	(text_box "The 10k potentiometer forms a voltage divider, creating an adjustable reference voltage that is buffered by the op-amp UxA, configured as a voltage follower, to isolate the reference signal from any input variations. "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 64.77 101.6 0)
		(size 50.8 26.67)
		(stroke
			(width 0.762)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "090a8516-bacb-4b43-8348-0e85b527c509")
	)
	(text_box "Provides variable gain by adjusting the feedback resistance using a 10k potentiometer. Op-amp UxC is in an inverting amplifier configuration and the gain is adjustable by varying the resistance of the potentiometer, allowing control over the output signal amplitude:\n\nVout = - ((R + RV) / RV) * Vin\nVout_rv10k = 1.10 * Vin \nVout_rv05k = 1.20 * Vin \nVout_rv03k = 1.33 * Vin \nVout_rv01k = 2.00 * Vin \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 168.91 101.6 0)
		(size 50.8 26.67)
		(stroke
			(width 0.762)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "0e9e6291-8a37-483d-afd9-52e166390f71")
	)
	(text_box "This is to feed the power rails of the quad op amp with a capacitor to decouple noise from the power supply."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 22.86 101.6 0)
		(size 40.64 26.67)
		(stroke
			(width 0.762)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "49d7f303-3107-40d5-9e58-ad4bbb0acdec")
	)
	(text_box "Attenuates high-frequency noise using a low-pass filter formed by the 1kΩ resistor and the 1μF capacitor. Op-amp UxD is configured as a buffer (voltage follower) to maintain signal integrity and ensure a stable filtered analog output.\n\nThe cut-off frequency is:\nfc = 1/(2*pi*R*C)\nfc = 159.15 Hz"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 220.98 101.6 0)
		(size 50.8 26.67)
		(stroke
			(width 0.762)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "5c60ded7-bdc2-4b38-b47e-c5b7cabd094f")
	)
	(text_box "Amplifies the difference between the input signal and the reference voltage. Op-amp UxB is configured in a differential amplifier configuration with 1kΩ resistors (unity gain). The circuit amplifies the differential signal while rejecting common-mode noise, with an output of Vout = V+ - V-.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 116.84 101.6 0)
		(size 50.8 26.67)
		(stroke
			(width 0.762)
			(type default)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "bcafc4de-2503-461e-9c3c-deba0b5e485a")
	)
